<br>
/target me<br>
/doability 4<br>
<br>
What happened was that because of lag (I suspect - it was in a nagafen fight) I didn't get targeted and ended up wasting my loh on nagafen.  <br>
<br>
So I created another one that looked like this for nagafen take 2:<br>
<br>
/target me<br>
/target me<br>
/target me<br>
/doability 4<br>
<br>
I figured that would ensure I was targeted.  So I hit my hotkey, got killed by nagafen and repoped at my bind spot in east freeport.  Then my loh went off and I was healed for zero hitpoints.  <br>
<br>
The whole idea of the hotkey is to reduce the time it takes to kick off the loh.  In situations where I know I'll be using it for myself I bring up the ability menu at about 50percent health and position the mouse over the button.  Then I rest my finger on the TAB key.  That hasn't failed me yet.  I really wish I could hotkey this reliably though. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><br><font color=#FFFFFF>- </font><a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bpaladinsofnorrath>Paladins of Norrath</a><font color=#FFFFFF> - </font><a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral>General</a> <font color=#FFFFFF> - </font><a href="http://eq.castersrealm.com/pon">Paladins of Norrath Homepage</a><font color=#FFFFFF> - </font><br><br><br><br>Powered By <a href=http://www.ezboard.com/>ezboard®</a> Ver. 6.8<br>Copyright ©1999-2001 ezboard, Inc.</center></body></html>  